SIMPLE: indiscretion
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Indiscretion
<hw>In`dis*cre"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>in-</ets> not + <ets>discretion</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>indiscr⟦eacute⟧tion</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or state of being indiscreet; lack of
discretion; imprudence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An indiscreet act; indiscreet behavior.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Past <qex>indiscretion</qex> is a venial crime.</q>
<rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Indiscriminate</ent>⟦br⟧
